data.name: CheckinArgument
desc: contains information needed to checkin a document.
The checkin command is always called on the target private working copy document.

items.name: MajorVersion
desc: Tells whether to create a new major or minor version during the checkin.

items.name: VersionComment
desc: Contains the version comment to set during the checkin.

items.name: SourceURL
desc: contains the URL of the source of the action (e.g.
the URL of the temporary file to checkin).

items.name: TargetURL
desc: contains the URL of the private working copy to checkin.

items.name: NewTitle
desc: contains the title of the transferred object, if it is different from the original one.
If this field is filled, for example, a file will be renamed while it is being checked in.

items.name: MimeType
desc: contains the Mime-Type of the content to check-in as it may be different from the original one.
